Ex parte William Hanley; and Ex parte John Welch. May 1, 1944.

The motions for leave to file petitions for writs of habeas corpus are denied. Ex parte Hawk, 321 U. S. 114, 117. Treating the papers as petitions for writs of certiorari to the Supreme Court of Illinois, the petitions are denied.
